  <thing id="fFierySpel" name="Fiery Spell" description="Your fire magic is bolstered, further scorching your enemies.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: A fiery spell deals an extra 1 point of fire damage for each die of damage the spell deals. This feat can be applied only to spells with the fire descriptor. For example, if a 9th-level wizard with this feat casts a fiery {i}fireball{/i}, the {i}fireball{/i} deals 9d6+9 points of damage. A fiery spell uses up a spell slot one level higher than the spell&#146;s actual level." compset="Feat" summary="Fire spl does +1 bonus fire dam per die. +1 Level." uniqueness="useronce">
