  <thing id="fRSnakeStr" name="Rattlesnake Strike" description="Having observed the ways of a desert viper, you have learned to use {i}ki{/i} in a fashion similar to poison.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Wis 15, Improved Initiative, Improved Unarmed Strike, Stunning Fist.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You must declare that you are using this feat before you make your attack roll (thus, a failed attack roll ruins the attempt). By expending one of your Stunning Fist uses for the day, you imbue your next unarmed attack with disruptive {i}ki{/i} that mimics the effects of mild viper venom. If that attack hits, it deals normal damage and forces the target to make a Fortitude saving throw (DC 10 + 1/2 your character level + your Wis modifier). A creature that fails the saving throw takes 1d3 points of Constitution damage and must make a similar saving throw 1 minute later or take another 1d3 points of Constitution damage. This feat can be used only once per round.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: A fighter may select Rattlesnake Strike as one of his fighter bonus feats." compset="Feat" summary="Use 1 stun, struck foe is poisoned for 1d3/1d3 Con (DCXX Fort neg)." uniqueness="useronce">
