  <thing id="xWaterSens" name="Water Sense" description="Bhukas have the innate ability to detect a source of drinkable water within a distance of 100 feet. Doing this requires a Survival check; the DC depends on the depth below ground of the water source, according to the following table.\n\n{b}Water Depth &#151;&#151; Survival DC{/b}\n0 feet (on the surface) &#151;&#151; 10\n10 feet or less &#151;&#151; 12\n11&#150;20 feet &#151;&#151; 15\n21&#150;40 feet &#151;&#151; 20\n41&#150;70 feet &#151;&#151; 25\n71&#150;100 feet &#151;&#151; 30" compset="Special" summary="Can make survival checks to detect water to depths of up to 100 ft.">
